n":0},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Prophets ordered to delay morning meal, hasten to break fast","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, we company of prophets have been commanded to delay our pre-fasting meal, to hasten to break our fast, and to place our rights hands over our left hands in prayer.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 1770\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27151,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/02\/07\/prophets-righteous-pure-hearts\/","url_meta":{"origin":25175,"position":1},"title":"Fudayl on Tazkiyyah: Prophets and righteous have pure hearts","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 7, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Nu\u2019aym reported: Fudayl ibn \u2018Iyad, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIt has been said that among the character of the prophets and chosen elect is the purity of their hearts. They are three characteristics: forbearance, penitence, and a portion of prayer in the night.\u201d Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304'\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31739,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/02\/honest-traders-prophets-truthful\/","url_meta":{"origin":25175,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Trade: Honest merchants with prophets, truthful, martyrs","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 2, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe honest and trustworthy merchant will be with the prophets, the truthful, and the martyrs.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1209 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24198,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/12\/18\/ilm-scholars-inheritors-prophets\/","url_meta":{"origin":25175,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Knowledge: Scholars are successors of prophets","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 18, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Darda reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe scholars are the successors of the prophets. Verily, the prophets do not pass on gold and silver coins, but rather they only impart knowledge.\u201d Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 10\/68 Grade: Salih (good) according to Al-Bazza\u0304r \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37727,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/02\/23\/prophets-rejoice-hardship\/","url_meta":{"origin":25175,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Prophets rejoice at hardship, seeking reward","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 23, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe most severely tested are the Prophets, and then the righteous. One of them would be tested with poverty until he could find nothing to cover himself but a cloak. One of them would rejoice\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7283,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/29\/prophets-righteous-severely-tested\/","url_meta":{"origin":25175,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Trials: The Prophets, righteous most severely tested","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 29, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa'd ibn Abi Waqqas reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, which people are tested most severely?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThey are the prophets, then the next best, then the next best. A man is put to trial according to his religion.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25175","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\